1
00:00:09,121 --> 00:00:09,917
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,294 --> 00:00:18,922
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,965 --> 00:00:22,126
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,802 --> 00:00:26,464
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,572 --> 00:00:30,200
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,910 --> 00:00:35,004
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,647 --> 00:00:38,775
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,252 --> 00:00:44,621
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,259 --> 00:00:49,022
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,127 --> 00:00:50,856
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,929 --> 00:00:53,261
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,563
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,635 --> 00:00:58,535
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,603 --> 00:01:01,037
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,941 --> 00:01:09,505
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,615 --> 00:01:13,106
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,885 --> 00:01:16,752
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,593 --> 00:01:22,890
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,363 --> 00:01:26,887
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:47,063 --> 00:01:49,293
<i>I think we almost finished</i>
<i>shaking off the losers.</i>

21
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:51,966
<i>Then I guess I'll move</i>
<i>onto the main issue.</i>

22
00:01:53,069 --> 00:01:55,401
<i>It has been 45 minutes, so I'll start.</i>

23
00:01:56,872 --> 00:01:57,634
All right!

24
00:01:58,908 --> 00:02:01,638
Here is the tenth question!

25
00:02:03,612 --> 00:02:04,510
<i>Here it comes!</i>

26
00:02:04,914 --> 00:02:07,781
<i>I have to put everything on</i>
<i>the line for this question!</i>

27
00:02:08,951 --> 00:02:14,856
<i>The Tenth Question. All or Nothing!</i>

28
00:02:17,660 --> 00:02:20,128
<i>Hmph! Making such a big deal.</i>

29
00:02:21,297 --> 00:02:23,458
<i>This is the final obstacle.</i>

30
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:26,458
<i>Kankuro, come back already!</i>

31
00:02:26,902 --> 00:02:30,463
<i>If he starts the tenth question,</i>
<i>your cheat sheet has no meaning!</i>

32
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:34,300
But before that,

33
00:02:35,177 --> 00:02:40,080
I'm going to add
some rules for the last question.

34
00:02:50,559 --> 00:02:53,027
Aren't you lucky?

35
00:02:55,464 --> 00:02:58,524
It looks like playing with
the dolls wasn't a waste, after all?

36
00:02:59,301 --> 00:03:00,165
<i>This guy.</i>

37
00:03:00,736 --> 00:03:02,465
<i>He's figured Crow out!</i>

38
00:03:03,606 --> 00:03:05,801
Anyway, sit down.

39
00:03:21,824 --> 00:03:23,519
Let me explain!

40
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,925
These are

41
00:03:27,563 --> 00:03:29,497
the hopeless rules!

42
00:03:33,903 --> 00:03:35,495
Well, anyhow.

43
00:03:35,938 --> 00:03:39,032
There's nothing to do when
the subordinates are gone, huh?

44
00:03:39,408 --> 00:03:43,071
Well, it'll get busy soon enough.

45
00:03:43,679 --> 00:03:44,611
Why?

46
00:03:46,916 --> 00:03:48,907
This year's first proctor...

47
00:03:49,084 --> 00:03:51,416
I hear it's that Ibiki Morino.

48
00:03:53,756 --> 00:03:56,623
<i>Well then, passing the first exam</i>
<i>already seems iffy.</i>

49
00:03:58,527 --> 00:04:01,394
Of all the people, that sadist...

50
00:04:01,931 --> 00:04:02,955
Sadist?

51
00:04:03,299 --> 00:04:09,465
Kurenai, you're a new Jonin,
so you wouldn't know.

52
00:04:11,173 --> 00:04:12,800
Who is this person?

53
00:04:14,210 --> 00:04:16,542
He is a pro, a professional.

54
00:04:17,112 --> 00:04:19,603
Professional? Of what?

55
00:04:26,021 --> 00:04:28,751
Torture and interrogation.

56
00:04:29,091 --> 00:04:29,887
What?!

57
00:04:30,793 --> 00:04:35,230
Well, there maybe no physical torture
in the exam itself,

58
00:04:35,464 --> 00:04:38,160
but he's sure to use his
his skills as an interrogator

59
00:04:38,234 --> 00:04:41,226
to torment them psychologically.

60
00:04:43,172 --> 00:04:44,264
That is...

61
00:04:45,608 --> 00:04:50,011
Leaf Village Anbu's
Torture and Interrogation Unit Marshall,

62
00:04:50,512 --> 00:04:52,036
Ibiki Morino!

63
00:04:56,418 --> 00:04:58,978
<i>Hopeless rules...?!</i>

64
00:05:00,623 --> 00:05:02,921
First, you guys will have to choose

65
00:05:03,292 --> 00:05:08,161
whether or not you will take
this 10th question!

66
00:05:08,731 --> 00:05:09,459
Huh?!

67
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,994
<i>Choose whether or not</i>
<i>to take the exam?</i>

68
00:05:15,271 --> 00:05:16,295
What, choose?!

69
00:05:16,538 --> 00:05:19,132
What happens if you choose not
to take the 10th exam?

70
00:05:19,675 --> 00:05:25,341
If you chose not to take the exam,
then your score will be zero.

71
00:05:26,582 --> 00:05:28,277
In other words, you fail!

72
00:05:28,917 --> 00:05:32,080
And of course, the same goes for
the two others in the same group!

73
00:05:32,621 --> 00:05:33,679
W-What does that mean!

74
00:05:33,756 --> 00:05:36,316
Of course, everybody is going to
choose to take the exam!

75
00:05:36,659 --> 00:05:38,923
This is ridiculous!
As if we have a choice!

76
00:05:39,395 --> 00:05:43,331
And... one more rule...

77
00:05:43,699 --> 00:05:44,631
<i>Another one?!</i>

78
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,497
<i>Finish with it already!</i>

79
00:05:47,569 --> 00:05:51,005
If you chose to take it and
are unable to answer it correctly,

80
00:05:51,774 --> 00:05:53,674
then you will have to...

81
00:05:55,344 --> 00:05:59,337
relinquish your right
of taking the Chunin Exam forever.

82
00:06:02,651 --> 00:06:04,676
What kind of ridiculous rule is that?!

83
00:06:05,154 --> 00:06:07,554
Besides, there are plenty
of people here

84
00:06:07,623 --> 00:06:09,488
who have taken the
Chunin Exam many times!

85
00:06:17,466 --> 00:06:20,458
You're just unlucky.

86
00:06:22,538 --> 00:06:24,802
I make the rule this year.

87
00:06:27,109 --> 00:06:30,442
But I did give you
the option to go back!

88
00:06:32,881 --> 00:06:36,248
For those of you who aren't confident,
you can choose not to take it

89
00:06:36,385 --> 00:06:39,081
and take the exam
next year or the year after that.

90
00:06:42,858 --> 00:06:44,325
<i>Oh! How terrible!</i>

91
00:06:45,027 --> 00:06:48,292
<i>If one out of the three</i>
<i>chooses not to take the exam,</i>

92
00:06:48,564 --> 00:06:50,623
<i>then all three will be failed.</i>

93
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:55,164
<i>If you do choose to take it,</i>
<i>but get the wrong answer...</i>

94
00:06:55,537 --> 00:06:57,835
<i>then that person will be a</i>
<i>Genin for the rest of their life!</i>

95
00:06:58,707 --> 00:07:00,572
<i>No matter what,</i>
<i>the odds are against us!</i>

96
00:07:01,443 --> 00:07:03,411
<i>It's an impossible choice</i>
<i>for anyone with normal nerves!</i>

97
00:07:08,884 --> 00:07:10,511
Then, let's begin...

98
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:13,647
The 10th question...

99
00:07:13,956 --> 00:07:16,550
Those who will not be taking it,
raise your hands!

100
00:07:17,826 --> 00:07:20,989
Once I confirm your number,
I'll ask you to leave!

101
00:07:27,269 --> 00:07:30,136
<i>What kind of a question</i>
<i>is it going to be...?</i>

102
00:07:30,839 --> 00:07:31,965
<i>Darn!</i>

103
00:07:32,174 --> 00:07:34,608
<i>If I get it wrong,</i>
<i>I'll be a Genin for the rest of my life.</i>

104
00:07:34,676 --> 00:07:35,734
<i>I don't want that!</i>

105
00:07:35,944 --> 00:07:38,174
<i>But if I choose not take it...!</i>

106
00:07:38,247 --> 00:07:42,240
<i>Then I'll fail Sasuke and Sakura, too!</i>
<i>I don't want that either!</i>

107
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,816
<i>I won't raise my hand!</i>

108
00:07:45,654 --> 00:07:48,782
<i>I'm confident that</i>
<i>I can answer it correctly.</i>

109
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:50,652
<i>But...</i>

110
00:07:52,227 --> 00:07:54,457
<i>But Naruto! You're different!</i>

111
00:07:55,330 --> 00:07:58,891
<i>You should retreat this time</i>
<i>even if it means to ignore us</i>

112
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:01,026
<i>and think of your next chance</i>
<i>to take the Exam!</i>

113
00:08:04,706 --> 00:08:08,164
I... I...

114
00:08:10,212 --> 00:08:12,407
I'm quitting!
I'm not going to take it!

115
00:08:13,982 --> 00:08:15,381
#50 failed!

116
00:08:16,518 --> 00:08:20,511
#130, #111 will be
failed as well...

117
00:08:22,057 --> 00:08:25,049
I-I'm sorry...
Gennai! Inaho!

118
00:08:28,330 --> 00:08:29,262
Darn...

119
00:08:29,965 --> 00:08:31,023
M-Me too!

120
00:08:33,569 --> 00:08:34,797
Me too!

121
00:08:46,215 --> 00:08:47,147
<i>Naruto...</i>

122
00:08:48,784 --> 00:08:50,684
<i>Why don't you raise your hand?</i>

123
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:56,985
<i>That guy...</i>

124
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:59,618
<i>I am the super elite ninja</i>

125
00:08:59,695 --> 00:09:01,458
<i>who will be carrying</i>
<i>the name of the Hokage!</i>

126
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:05,660
<i>My name is Naruto Uzumaki,</i>
<i>remember that!</i>

127
00:09:06,168 --> 00:09:08,033
<i>Shut up!</i>

128
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:12,297
<i>I'm prepared to do anything</i>
<i>to become a Hokage!</i>

129
00:09:12,774 --> 00:09:14,139
<i>I will surpass the Hokage!</i>

130
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:17,172
<i>And I will make all of</i>
<i>the people in the village</i>

131
00:09:17,246 --> 00:09:19,714
<i>acknowledge my presence!</i>

132
00:09:24,253 --> 00:09:26,847
<i>He's always got such a one track mind.</i>

133
00:09:26,922 --> 00:09:29,447
<i>Saying Hokage, Hokage</i>
<i>all the time like a fool.</i>

134
00:09:32,761 --> 00:09:34,353
<i>I'm sorry, Naruto.</i>

135
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,695
<i>It seems like...</i>

136
00:09:36,765 --> 00:09:38,892
<i>I don't want to...</i>

137
00:09:42,304 --> 00:09:43,896
<i>crush your unachievable dreams.</i>

138
00:10:22,411 --> 00:10:23,241
That guy...

139
00:10:26,148 --> 00:10:29,481
Ibiki completely understands how
the human psyche works.

140
00:10:30,486 --> 00:10:33,353
And the most horrifying part is...

141
00:10:34,123 --> 00:10:39,823
that by cornering people psychologically
he controls their psyche and

142
00:10:40,997 --> 00:10:44,899
reveals the fundamental
weakness of a human.

143
00:10:55,411 --> 00:10:58,175
Don't underestimate me!
I won't run!

144
00:10:59,882 --> 00:11:00,940
I'll take it!

145
00:11:01,450 --> 00:11:03,611
But even if I'm stuck being
a Genin forever,

146
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:07,519
I will become a Hokage
no matter what it takes!

147
00:11:10,826 --> 00:11:12,691
I'm not scared!

148
00:11:19,969 --> 00:11:24,201
<i>That guy, he wasn't even</i>
<i>thinking of us at all.</i>

149
00:11:25,041 --> 00:11:26,599
<i>Such audacity!</i>

150
00:11:27,176 --> 00:11:28,268
<i>That's right...</i>

151
00:11:28,644 --> 00:11:30,669
<i>That's exactly the kind of fool you are!</i>

152
00:11:32,982 --> 00:11:34,609
I'll ask again.

153
00:11:36,152 --> 00:11:38,279
It's a choice that will alter your life.

154
00:11:39,121 --> 00:11:40,850
If you want to quit, now is your chance!

155
00:11:41,490 --> 00:11:44,288
I'm not going to take back
my words!

156
00:11:44,827 --> 00:11:46,351
That is my Way of Ninja!

157
00:11:55,371 --> 00:11:58,169
<i>Huh... What a funny kid.</i>

158
00:11:58,908 --> 00:12:02,400
<i>He completely brushed away</i>
<i>those kids' anxieties.</i>

159
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:08,940
<i>78, huh? Much more left</i>
<i>than I expected.</i>

160
00:12:10,119 --> 00:12:12,849
<i>It's going to be the same.</i>
<i>No matter how much more I push it.</i>

161
00:12:21,230 --> 00:12:22,595
I like your determination!

162
00:12:23,566 --> 00:12:24,396
Then...

163
00:12:25,501 --> 00:12:27,401
For those who are still here...

164
00:12:28,537 --> 00:12:30,095
The first exam...

165
00:12:33,275 --> 00:12:35,209
You have passed it!

166
00:12:41,784 --> 00:12:42,580
Huh?

167
00:12:43,953 --> 00:12:46,319
H-Hey, what does that mean?

168
00:12:46,555 --> 00:12:48,386
All of a sudden you're telling us
that we've passed!

169
00:12:48,457 --> 00:12:49,822
What about the 10th question?

170
00:12:52,661 --> 00:12:55,129
There wasn't such
a thing to begin with!

171
00:12:55,598 --> 00:12:58,897
Well, you can look at the choice you
just had to make as the 10th question!

172
00:12:59,401 --> 00:13:00,060
What?!

173
00:13:00,369 --> 00:13:01,233
Hey!

174
00:13:02,037 --> 00:13:04,972
Then, what were all
those nine questions for!

175
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,405
It was just a waste of time!

176
00:13:06,475 --> 00:13:07,908
Not a waste...

177
00:13:08,577 --> 00:13:12,980
The objective of the nine questions
were already accomplished.

178
00:13:14,517 --> 00:13:19,819
To test your individual ability
to gather information!

179
00:13:21,056 --> 00:13:23,024
Ability to gather information?

180
00:13:23,792 --> 00:13:24,520
First...

181
00:13:25,227 --> 00:13:27,127
The focus of this test was

182
00:13:27,196 --> 00:13:29,494
on the system of determining
the pass or failure

183
00:13:29,565 --> 00:13:33,934
based on the three person groups
that was proposed in the first rule.

184
00:13:34,803 --> 00:13:36,168
By grading the exam on
a group basis,

185
00:13:36,238 --> 00:13:42,074
I added the unimaginable pressure
of dragging down your teammates.

186
00:13:43,779 --> 00:13:44,768
I see, I see.

187
00:13:44,847 --> 00:13:48,146
I kind of felt that was
the point of this test!

188
00:13:48,884 --> 00:13:50,215
<i>No, you didn't!</i>

189
00:13:52,955 --> 00:13:53,751
However...

190
00:13:54,256 --> 00:13:56,247
The questions on these tests weren't
things that

191
00:13:56,325 --> 00:13:59,123
you Genin Ninja would
have been able to solve...

192
00:14:00,062 --> 00:14:02,360
So in that case...

193
00:14:02,965 --> 00:14:06,492
I imagined that most of you here
would have come to this conclusion:

194
00:14:06,569 --> 00:14:09,800
"In order to score points,
I'll have to cheat."

195
00:14:10,873 --> 00:14:11,703
In other words,

196
00:14:11,774 --> 00:14:14,971
this exam was created under the premise
that you all would cheat!

197
00:14:25,721 --> 00:14:28,747
That being said,

198
00:14:28,824 --> 00:14:31,884
I had two Chunin in the group
who knew all of the answers

199
00:14:31,961 --> 00:14:35,021
from whom you could cheat.

200
00:14:35,331 --> 00:14:38,789
<i>What?! That's what it was?</i>

201
00:14:39,268 --> 00:14:41,395
I had a hard time figuring
out the guy.

202
00:14:41,470 --> 00:14:43,131
Yeah. Really...

203
00:14:45,541 --> 00:14:47,270
It was so obvious!

204
00:14:47,343 --> 00:14:49,368
There's something wrong with you
if you didn't notice!

205
00:14:49,445 --> 00:14:51,037
Right, Hinata?!

206
00:14:51,780 --> 00:14:55,375
<i>He...didn't realize it...</i>

207
00:14:55,884 --> 00:14:57,181
However...

208
00:14:58,053 --> 00:15:02,513
those who just foolishly cheated,
naturally were disqualified.

209
00:15:04,660 --> 00:15:05,991
That's because...

210
00:15:06,462 --> 00:15:08,953
Information, depending on
the time and situation,

211
00:15:09,031 --> 00:15:11,397
it will be more valuable than life.

212
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:13,601
And in a mission or on a battlefield,

213
00:15:15,604 --> 00:15:18,164
you will always have to risk your life
to fight for it!

214
00:15:20,142 --> 00:15:24,306
Horrible burn marks, nail punctures
and scratches...

215
00:15:25,180 --> 00:15:26,511
Those are signs of physical torture!

216
00:15:31,687 --> 00:15:33,279
When information is gathered

217
00:15:33,355 --> 00:15:35,448
and the enemy or a third party
finds out about it,

218
00:15:35,591 --> 00:15:38,992
that information is no longer
guaranteed to be correct.

219
00:15:41,363 --> 00:15:43,297
Just remember this.

220
00:15:45,134 --> 00:15:47,659
To be given the wrong information

221
00:15:48,037 --> 00:15:51,529
can bring a catastrophic blow
to your friends and town.

222
00:15:53,042 --> 00:15:56,102
So that is why, out of necessity,
we forced you guys to cheat

223
00:15:56,178 --> 00:15:58,578
in order to test your ability
to collect information.

224
00:15:59,615 --> 00:16:04,552
And we filtered out those who
were clearly lacking in those abilities.

225
00:16:05,254 --> 00:16:06,152
But...

226
00:16:06,555 --> 00:16:09,615
The last question doesn't
make any sense.

227
00:16:10,059 --> 00:16:11,253
However...

228
00:16:12,361 --> 00:16:16,764
this 10th question was
the main issue of this first exam.

229
00:16:17,232 --> 00:16:17,857
Huh?

230
00:16:18,267 --> 00:16:20,132
What do you mean?

231
00:16:20,736 --> 00:16:21,930
I'll explain.

232
00:16:22,471 --> 00:16:26,032
The tenth question was to
take on the question, or not.

233
00:16:27,242 --> 00:16:31,804
Needless to say, it is
a painful decision to make.

234
00:16:32,648 --> 00:16:33,842
Those who chose not to
take on the question,

235
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:36,214
would be immediately failed
along with their whole squad!

236
00:16:36,552 --> 00:16:40,750
Those who chose to answer
the question and got it wrong...

237
00:16:41,423 --> 00:16:44,415
would be robbed of their chance
to take the Exam forever.

238
00:16:45,227 --> 00:16:48,128
It really is an unfair question.

239
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:54,101
Then, how about these two choices?

240
00:16:54,970 --> 00:16:57,632
Let's say that you guys did
become a Chunin.

241
00:16:58,707 --> 00:17:01,267
The mission is to steal
a secret document!

242
00:17:03,045 --> 00:17:04,535
You have no idea how many
Ninjas the enemy has,

243
00:17:04,613 --> 00:17:07,912
their ability, and other armament
they may have.

244
00:17:08,884 --> 00:17:13,048
On top of that, there maybe
the pitfall of an enemy trap.

245
00:17:13,722 --> 00:17:17,317
Now this mission...
Will you take it? Or not take it?

246
00:17:17,860 --> 00:17:19,327
Because you want your life spared...

247
00:17:19,595 --> 00:17:21,927
Because your partners will
be put in danger...

248
00:17:22,731 --> 00:17:24,995
Can you get away from
dangerous missions?

249
00:17:26,034 --> 00:17:27,058
The answer is...

250
00:17:30,305 --> 00:17:30,964
No!

251
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,775
There are going to be missions
you cannot avoid

252
00:17:34,843 --> 00:17:36,811
no matter how risky or
dangerous it may be!

253
00:17:39,648 --> 00:17:42,173
Showing your courage to
your teammates in a tight spot,

254
00:17:42,851 --> 00:17:45,081
and the ability to get through
the hardships...

255
00:17:48,290 --> 00:17:51,953
This is the quality that is needed
in a Chunin troop leader!

256
00:17:56,598 --> 00:18:00,967
In a pinch, there are
those who cannot risk their own fate,

257
00:18:01,403 --> 00:18:05,237
and those who waver and give up
their chances

258
00:18:05,307 --> 00:18:09,368
because they think they
will have another chance.

259
00:18:10,212 --> 00:18:13,375
I believe that such fools who don't have
strong determination

260
00:18:13,949 --> 00:18:18,010
have no right to become a Chunin!

261
00:18:19,488 --> 00:18:21,353
For those of you who chose
to take on the question,

262
00:18:21,423 --> 00:18:24,688
you can say that you have successfully
answered the difficult 10th question!

263
00:18:26,161 --> 00:18:29,528
You shall be able to take on
the adversity that may lie in your way.

264
00:18:31,366 --> 00:18:32,993
You've passed through the gates!

265
00:18:34,303 --> 00:18:37,761
The fist exam for the Chunin Exam
has been completed.

266
00:18:38,907 --> 00:18:41,808
I wish you well!

267
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:44,638
All right! Wish us well!

268
00:18:44,746 --> 00:18:47,271
I did it! I did it!
Yeaah!

269
00:18:49,251 --> 00:18:50,411
<i>What a funny guy...</i>

270
00:19:01,497 --> 00:19:02,964
W-What's going on?!

271
00:19:07,236 --> 00:19:09,170
<i>Gosh, this one...</i>

272
00:19:09,671 --> 00:19:11,070
You guys!

273
00:19:11,139 --> 00:19:14,006
This isn't the time to be
celebrating!

274
00:19:15,377 --> 00:19:18,835
I'm the proctor for the second exam!
Anko Mitarashi!

275
00:19:19,882 --> 00:19:22,112
Let's move onto
the next stage! Next!

276
00:19:22,451 --> 00:19:24,442
Follow me!

277
00:19:30,926 --> 00:19:32,450
Read the atmosphere.

278
00:19:35,764 --> 00:19:39,063
<i>This proctor...</i>
<i>Is kind of like Naruto.</i>

279
00:19:40,002 --> 00:19:44,837
78?! Ibiki!
You let 26 teams slide by?

280
00:19:45,507 --> 00:19:48,874
I guess, the first exam this time around
was too easy.

281
00:19:49,244 --> 00:19:52,771
It seems like this time,
there are a lot of excellent candidates.

282
00:19:53,215 --> 00:19:55,877
Huh! Well, all right...

283
00:19:56,752 --> 00:20:00,688
I'll drop more than half of them
in the second exam!

284
00:20:01,256 --> 00:20:03,622
M-More than half?

285
00:20:04,326 --> 00:20:06,886
I'm getting excited.

286
00:20:07,629 --> 00:20:09,392
I'll give you the details tomorrow.

287
00:20:09,464 --> 00:20:11,091
We'll be changing locations,

288
00:20:11,266 --> 00:20:15,259
so get information from your Jonin
about the location and the time!

289
00:20:16,204 --> 00:20:18,001
That's it. You're dismissed.

290
00:20:38,026 --> 00:20:41,393
<i>I didn't think that there would be a guy</i>
<i>that would pass with a blank sheet.</i>

291
00:20:42,197 --> 00:20:46,429
<i>Naruto Uzumaki...</i>
<i>He really is a funny guy.</i>

292
00:20:51,173 --> 00:20:53,641
W-What is this place?!

293
00:20:53,742 --> 00:20:55,642
NO TRESPASSING

294
00:21:02,784 --> 00:21:05,651
This is the location for
the "second exam",

295
00:21:05,721 --> 00:21:08,554
the 44th Training Field.

296
00:21:09,825 --> 00:21:12,817
Also known as... the Forest of Death.

297
00:21:15,197 --> 00:21:17,495
The Forest of... Death?!

298
00:22:52,496 --> 00:22:54,361
I passed the first exam!

299
00:22:54,664 --> 00:22:57,360
I'm just going to hop, jump
and take a big step and...

300
00:22:57,434 --> 00:22:59,493
Huh? Konohamaru and the gang?

301
00:22:59,736 --> 00:23:00,998
Hey, you guys!

302
00:23:01,071 --> 00:23:02,629
If you want to play a Ninja game...

303
00:23:03,106 --> 00:23:07,202
No? What?
You came here for a mission?!

304
00:23:08,311 --> 00:23:13,715
Next episode:
"Special Report:
Live from the Forest of Death!"

305
00:23:13,917 --> 00:23:16,750
As for me, I'm going to kick butt again!
